H0.text: Elevation is the height above or below sea level.

H1.text: Depth is the term used to describe the height above or below sea level.

H2.text: Latitude is the term used to describe the height above or below sea level.

H3.text: Variation is the height above or below sea level.

A4.text: The term elevation is mainly used when referring to points on the Earth's surface, while altitude or geopotential height is used for points above the surface, and depth is used for points below the surface.

A5.text: The elevation of a geographic location is its height above or below a fixed reference point, most commonly a reference geoid, a mathematical model of the Earth's sea level as an equipotential gravitational surface.
